spans.text: — An aged father's wounds to heal , Through scenes of death I flew
to bless These aged eyes once more
Those tears a father ill can bear
by thy kind pity , take The blessings of his child
are the dear illusions fled Which soothed my former hours
that fancy spread , Ah , vainly spread with flowers
that , pierced with ghastly wounds , My venturous lover fell ! — " My sorrows shall with life endure
that sure My life will not be long
It's EDWARD bids thy griefs be over
dear to my AMELIA'S breast , Since valued still by thee !
will his power restrain The ties my soul would bind
his power restrain The ties my soul would bind
